name: 03-Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
content:
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Data Profiling:

  • Statistical summaries of revenue, call patterns, churn rates.
  • Missing value distributions and frequency tables for categorical features.

Descriptive Analysis:

  • Revenue Distributions – Monthly revenue histograms and boxplots.
  • Service Usage – Distributions of roaming calls, dropped calls, and customer care interactions.
  • Customer Demographics – Age group, income group, months in service.
  • Churn Analysis – Churn rates by revenue group, service usage, and region.
  • Occupation-wise Revenue – Average monthly revenue by occupation.

Insights from EDA:

  • High CustomerCareCalls often correlated with higher churn.
  • Younger age groups and high OverageMinutes customers showed higher churn likelihood.
  • High-revenue clusters were more stable with fewer dropped calls and lower churn.
